Leading South African ICT and telecoms operator, Vox presented its hosting and security products at the 2018 MyBroadband Cloud, Hosting, and Security Conference, which took place at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Midrand on 13 June. “We showcased our hosting environment, with our methodologies about how we migrate, manage, and look after our cloud portfolio as well as our security strategy,” said Mayleen Bywater, Senior Product Manager – Security at Vox. The MyBroadband Cloud Conference provides IT executives, managers, and business owners from various industries with a platform to interact and do business with South Africa’s top cloud and hosting providers. For more information, watch the video below of Vox at the conference.  This article was published in partnership with Vox.